Land-then-Transport
===================

This repository implements the method described in:

  Jingwen Fu, Ming Xiao, Mikael Skoglund, and Dong In Kim,
  "Land-then-transport: A Flow Matching-Based Generative Decoder for
  Wireless Image Transmission," accepted for publication in
  IEEE Transactions on Wireless Communications, 2026.

Upstream flow-matching implementation
-------------------------------------

This project is based on and substantially modifies:

  Keishi Ishihara, "Flow Matching in PyTorch"
  https://github.com/keishihara/flow-matching

The upstream project is distributed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0. Its license
is retained as the root LICENSE file. Modifications include wireless
channel-aware schedules and decoding, AWGN/Rayleigh/MIMO processing,
image-transmission training and evaluation, portable configuration,
and checkpoint handling.

Meta flow_matching
------------------

flow_matching/solver.py adapts components from:

  Meta Platforms, Inc., flow_matching
  https://github.com/facebookresearch/flow_matching

The corresponding CC BY-NC 4.0 license is included at
third_party/LICENSE-meta-flow-matching.

